Taylor meets west <PLACE continent="AF" form="NAM" gazref="TIPSTER:2777 IGDB:30002777" id="Pl-13" mod="W" type="CONTINENT">African</PLACE> envoys on exile call

<TEXT>

<PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-1" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">MONROVIA</PLACE>, Aug 2 (AFP)

<PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2133518 IGDB:17866482" id="Pl-6" latLong="6.500°N 9.500°W" type="COUNTRY">Liberia</PLACE>'s embattled president, Charles Taylor, began meeting Saturday
with a west <PLACE continent="AF" form="NAM" gazref="TIPSTER:2777 IGDB:30002777" id="Pl-14" mod="W" type="CONTINENT">African</PLACE> ministerial delegation which has travelled to
<PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-2" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">Monrovia</PLACE> to demand he step down and head into exile.

Taylor and his vice-president Moses Blah met with a team led by
Mohamed ibn Chambas, executive secretary of the Economic Community of
West <PLACE continent="AF" form="NAM" gazref="TIPSTER:2777 IGDB:30002777" id="Pl-15" mod="W" type="CONTINENT">African</PLACE> States (ECOWAS), at the president's official residence
in the besieged <PLACE CTV="CITY" country="LR" form="NOM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-17" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">city</PLACE>.

The <PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2133518 IGDB:17866482" id="Pl-7" latLong="6.500°N 9.500°W" type="COUNTRY">Liberian</PLACE> leader had been expected to meet the ECOWAS party on
Friday, but failed to turn up, annoying some members of the
delegation.

Arriving at the meeting, Taylor angrily denied that he had tried to
avoid the envoys. &quot;I'm not running away,&quot; he said, accusing the media
of lying about his absence the previous day.

Aides claimed Taylor had travelled to the port city of <PLACE CTV="CITY" country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2130737 IGDB:17869263" id="Pl-18" latLong="5.881°N 10.047°W" state="GB" type="PPL">Buchanan</PLACE>, a
short distance south of the <PLACE country="LR" form="NOM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-11" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">capital</PLACE>, one of the frontlines in his war
with two rebel armies who control four fifths of the <PLACE country="LR" form="NOM" gazref="NGA:-2133518 IGDB:17866482" id="Pl-10" latLong="6.500°N 9.500°W" type="COUNTRY">country</PLACE>.

The ECOWAS delegation included <PLACE country="GH" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2073393 IGDB:17926607" id="Pl-19" latLong="8.000°N 2.000°W" type="COUNTRY">Ghana</PLACE>'s Foreign Minister Addo Akufo
Addo, the <PLACE country="NG" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2020891 IGDB:17979109" id="Pl-20" latLong="10.000°N 8.000°E" type="COUNTRY">Nigerian</PLACE> minister for cooperation and integration Lawan
Gana Guba and the <PLACE country="TG" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-1499563 IGDB:18500437" id="Pl-23" latLong="8.000°N 1.167°E" type="COUNTRY">Togolese</PLACE> defense minister General Assani Tidjani.

<PLACE country="NG" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2020891 IGDB:17979109" id="Pl-21" latLong="10.000°N 8.000°E" type="COUNTRY">Nigeria</PLACE> has offered Taylor political asylum if he agrees to resign
his post and allow international mediators to broker an agreement to
end <PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2133518 IGDB:17866482" id="Pl-8" latLong="6.500°N 9.500°W" type="COUNTRY">Liberia</PLACE>'s latest four-year bout of civil war.

A 1,500-strong advance guard of <PLACE country="NG" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2020891 IGDB:17979109" id="Pl-22" latLong="10.000°N 8.000°E" type="COUNTRY">Nigerian</PLACE> peacekeepers is due to start
arriving in <PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-3" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">Monrovia</PLACE> on Monday, and ECOWAS has given Taylor an
ultimatum that he must leave office within three days of the
soldiers' arrival.

But even as the warlord-turned-president arrived at his official
residence, intense fighting was continuing on the frontline in the
<PLACE country="LR" form="NOM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-12" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">capital</PLACE>, an AFP reporter at the scene said.

<PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:-2133518 IGDB:17866482" id="Pl-9" latLong="6.500°N 9.500°W" type="COUNTRY">Liberian</PLACE> government forces fought their way across two frontline
bridges in the capital <PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-4" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">Monrovia</PLACE> in what commanders said was an
offensive aimed a recapturing the <PLACE CTV="CITY" country="LR" form="NOM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-24" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" state="MO" type="PPLC">city</PLACE>'s rebel-held port.

Loyalist troops crossed the two key bridges, the site of a two-week
standoff with rebels, under a heavy barrage of rocket and mortar fire
and entered <PLACE CTV="TOWN" country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="NGA:120641 IGDB:20120641" id="Pl-25" latLong="6.631°N 10.250°W" state="MO" type="PPL">Via Town</PLACE>, a <PLACE CTV="TOWN" country="LR" form="NOM" gazref="NGA:120641 IGDB:20120641" id="Pl-26" latLong="6.631°N 10.250°W" state="MO" type="PPL">city district</PLACE> separating central <PLACE country="LR" form="NAM" gazref="IGDB:17865988 NGA:-2134012" id="Pl-5" latLong="6.311°N 10.805°W" mod="C" state="MO" type="PPLC">Monrovia</PLACE>
from the <PLACE country="NG" form="NOM" id="Pl-28" state="GB" type="RGN">port area</PLACE>.

Several houses could be seen burning in <PLACE CTV="TOWN" country="LR" form="NOM" gazref="NGA:120641 IGDB:20120641" id="Pl-27" latLong="6.631°N 10.250°W" state="MO" type="PPL">Via Town</PLACE> as the fighting
raged. Government officers on the ground said the offensive was aimed
at securing the port to allow west <PLACE continent="AF" form="NAM" gazref="TIPSTER:2777 IGDB:30002777" id="Pl-16" mod="W" type="CONTINENT">African</PLACE> peacekeepers to bring in
men and equipment.

</TEXT>









